claim.claim-text:
A spray dryer absorption system (18) for flue gas impurity reduction CHARACTERIZED by

a vessel (22) defining an interior chamber (22a) of approximately 12 meters or larger in diameter;

one or more dispersers (24, 26, 28, 30) arranged in a roof (32) of the interior chamber (22a);

an atomizer (34) for atomization and dispersal of absorption liquid or a reagent slurry droplets therefrom, centered within the disperser (24, 26, 28, 30) and surrounded by a flow directing device (36, 38, 40, 42); and

the flow directing device (36, 38, 40, 42) comprising three annular channels (60, 62, 64) formed concentrically around the atomizer (34) for a flow of flue gas therethrough, wherein an inner channel (60) reduces scale formation on a shroud (34a) of the disperser (24, 26, 28, 30), a middle channel (62) increases droplet rotational momentum and flue gas FG penetration, and an outer channel (64) reduces scale formation on walls (22b) of the interior chamber (22a).

A method of using a spray dryer absorption system (18) for flue gas FG impurity reduction CHARACTERIZED by

providing a vessel (22) defining an interior chamber (22a) of approximately 12 meters or larger in diameter;

arranging one or more dispersers (24, 26, 28, 30) in a roof (32) of the interior chamber (22a);

centering an atomizer (34) for atomization and dispersal of absorption liquid or a reagent slurry droplets therefrom, within the disperser (24, 26, 28, 30); and

surrounding the atomizer (34) with a flow directing device (36, 38, 40, 42) comprising three annular channels (60, 62, 64) formed concentrically around the atomizer (34) for a flow of flue gas FG therethrough, wherein an inner channel (60) reduces scale formation on a shroud (34a) of the disperser (24, 26, 28, 30), a middle channel (62) increases droplet rotational momentum and flue gas FG penetration, and an outer channel (64) reduces scale formation on walls (22b) of the interior chamber (22a), wherein droplets absorb impurities from the flue gas FG for flue gas FG impurity reduction.
